{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require food labelled as \"gluten-free\" on menus to be cross-contamination free",
        "additional_details": "I was diagnosed with coeliac disease last year, which has transformed my life and that of my family. Our food costs have tripled, and eating out is a minefield. Many places label food as \u201cgluten-free\u201d but cross-contamination makes it unsafe for those with coeliac disease, for example due to shared fryers and equipment.",
        "background": "Restaurants can label food as \u201cgluten-free\u201d on menus even if cooked where cross-contamination occurs, making it unsafe for people with coeliac disease or gluten intolerance. We ask the Government to strengthen the law so that gluten-free food must be prepared to avoid cross-contamination.",
